        "content": "<p>Hi All, I have a doubt on FHIR charset support.<br>\nAs per <a href=\"https://www.hl7.org/fhir/v3/Charset/cs.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.hl7.org/fhir/v3/Charset/cs.html\">https://www.hl7.org/fhir/v3/Charset/cs.html</a> FHIR supports UTF 8 only.<br>\nAs per <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/languages.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/languages.html\">http://hl7.org/fhir/languages.html</a>, we can provide content in specific language for example: Chinese which is UTF 16<br>\nSo how can we conclude about FHIR charset support here?</p>",
        "id": 169372777,
        "sender_full_name": "Sarvesh Padwal",
        "timestamp": 1561964475
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can do Chinese using UTF-8</p>",
        "id": 169399085,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1561990657
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Or any other language)</p>",
        "id": 169399098,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1561990671
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191320\">@Lloyd McKenzie</span><br>\nExample: <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/patient-example-chinese.json.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/patient-example-chinese.json.html\">http://hl7.org/fhir/patient-example-chinese.json.html</a><br>\nFor above example, As per FHIR specification,  we have to make it <strong>Content-Type: application/fhir+json;charset=UTF-8</strong><br>\n I think If we do Chinese using UTF-8, then some information may be lost.</p>",
        "id": 169454809,
        "sender_full_name": "Sarvesh Padwal",
        "timestamp": 1562046265
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8</a></p>",
